title: Fyodor Selin
data: Fyodor Ilyich Selin (Russian: Фёдор Ильич Селин; 7 March 1899 – 8 October 1960) was a Soviet football player and coach. Selin made his debut for USSR on 16 November 1924 in a friendly against Turkey. This biographical article relating to Soviet association football is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.
